subSubSection.paragraph:
(not referring to characters commonly seen in the foregoing species, 
L. ayarpathaensis
). Adult male.Head. Supracervical setae 10-15; postocular setae 12-13; occipital setae 11-13. Occiput, ocellar triangle and fronto-orbital plates brownish yellow. Antennal pedicel light brownish yellow; first flagellomere light grey; arista with 3-4 dorsal and 1-2 ventral branches in addition to terminal fork. Gena and clypeus brownish yellow. Cibarial medial sensilla 22-23; posterior sensilla approximately 16.
